/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 50 760 Tm (AOXCON WHITEPAPER) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 745 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 730 Tm (ABSTRACT) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 715 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 700 Tm (AOXCON standardizes a deterministic interoperability kernel for EVM, Move and Cardano. The protocol separates chain-agnostic domain logic from chain-specific adapters and enforces canonical message and error semantics.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 685 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 670 Tm (MOTIVATION) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 655 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 640 Tm (Multi-chain products often fail when each chain implementation drifts in behavior. AOXCON removes drift by defining one canonical model that all adapters must implement.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 625 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 610 Tm (ARCHITECTURE SUMMARY) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 595 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 580 Tm (AOXCON uses a layered model:) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 565 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 550 Tm (1. domain core,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 535 Tm (2. chain adapters,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 520 Tm (3. verification and relayer,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 505 Tm (4. SDK interface.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 490 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 475 Tm (The domain core governs state transitions and canonical status codes. Adapters map runtime specifics but do not alter protocol decisions.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 460 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 445 Tm (CANONICAL PROCESSING) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 430 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 415 Tm (Messages are processed through strict ordered checks:) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 400 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 385 Tm (- schema,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 370 Tm (- chain namespace,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 355 Tm (- time window,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 340 Tm (- replay controls,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 325 Tm (- payload hash,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 310 Tm (- proof,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 295 Tm (- authorization,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 280 Tm (- transition execution.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 265 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 250 Tm (This order ensures deterministic decisions and clear security boundaries.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 235 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 220 Tm (SECURITY POSTURE) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 205 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 190 Tm (AOXCON mandates replay resistance, proof validation, role separation, bounded inputs and emergency controls. Audit readiness is measured through reproducible conformance evidence.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 175 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 160 Tm (ECOSYSTEM COMPATIBILITY) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 145 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 130 Tm (The compatibility contract binds `aoxcon-core`, adapters, relayer and SDK repositories to one behavior model and one SemVer compatibility policy.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 115 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 100 Tm (CONCLUSION) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 85 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 70 Tm (AOXCON is designed as the protocol kernel for a fully aligned EVM + Move + Cardano system, enabling deterministic interoperability and audit-grade governance.) Tj
